          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 12Be reaction products were deflected by",
                "a large-gap sweeper magnet and identified from",
                "energy-loss and time-of-flight measurements."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were detected using MoNA array. The",
                "MoNA consists of 144 individual detector modules. Each",
                "module is based on a 200 x 10 x 10 cm3 block of BC-408",
                "plastic scintillator. In the nominal configuration the",
                "vertical layers of 16 of the scintillator blocks give",
                "a detector volume of 2.0 x 1.6 x 0.9 m3. Neutron energy",
                "and position was determined from time of flight."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between charged particle reaction",
                "products and neutrons were required."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Momentum and energy of neutrons were determined",
                "from time of flight measurement"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Primary beam 18-O with energy of 120MeV/A bombarded a",
                "2.5 g/cm2 9Be production target. The A1900 fragment",
                "separator was used to separate and select the 13B",
                "secondary beam. The final energy of the beam was 71",
                "MeV/A, with an intensity of approximately 8.0E+5",
                "particles per second and a purity of 96%. 13Be was",
                "produced in a nucleon exchange reaction and immediately",
                "decayed into 12Be + n."
              ]
            }
          ],
